<p>The <code>field</code> tag retrieves a single field value from the database.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre>{open}field "column from table where condition"{close}</pre>

<h2>Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}field "name from users where id = 1"{close}
{open}field "count(*) from orders"{close}
{open}field "email from users where username = 'admin'"{close}</pre>

<h2>PHP Variable Method</h2>
<pre>// In PHP:
$userName = db("field name from users where id = 1");

// In template:
{open}$userName{close}</pre>

<h2>Direct Template Method</h2>
<pre>User count: {open}field "count(*) from users"{close}</pre>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Returns a single scalar value from the first matching row.</p>
<p>Requires database connection configured in $padSql* variables.</p>
